Summary of Shakespeareâs theater:
Shakespeareâs theater was called the globe
Supported by church
Open-air playhouse

Theaters were placed near bloody sports like bull baiting or bear baiting -> lower class
Vagabond and sturdy beggars
Shakespeare was also actor: played the Ghost in Hamlet
Later played at Blackfriars
Far more expensive
No curtain to indicate change of scenes
Different characters
Or make it clear with the dialogues/setting
Not many props/scenery  -> relied on hand gestures/dialogues -> bare stage
Performance not limited to the stage
The ghost (beneath the stage)
Polonius (behind the hangings)
No women in acting companies
Boys performed as women
Shakespeareâs acting company competed against all-boy acting companies
Shakespeare won
